    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1902-07-12T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1902-07-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="558"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d558">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hay</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Choate</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1902-07-12">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 12, 1902</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 956.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: The minister of the United States at Habana, in
                    his No. 45, of the 28th ultimo, writes that Mr. Lionel Carden, His British
                    Majesty’s minister resident at that city, and formerly consul-general there,
                    acted for this Government at the request of the War Department during the period
                    of intervention by the United States and also since the establishment of the
                    Cuban Republic.</p>
                <p>You are instructed to express to His Majesty’s Government this Government’s
                    appreciation of and thanks for Mr. Carden’s kindness and courtesy in the
                    matter.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">John Hay.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
